Unfortunately there's no easy path anon. It's a common saying among writers that you've got about a million words of terrible dogshit writing to get out of your system before you learn how to wryt gud. Writing is rewriting. Don't write in a vacuum, either. Get feedback. Write shit, leave it for a day, and come back to it, and see if anything bad sticks out at you in particular while the urge to throw it and then yourself in the garbage can overwhelms you.

The number one thing between you and being a good writer is putting in a shitload of hours just writing.
